# 3.4 Request Lifecycle

The lifecycle of a user request can be understood as a sequence of reasoning and execution steps.

Example request:

> "I want to study Artificial Intelligence in Germany."

The processing flow is:

```
User

↓

Flask receives request

↓

server.py

↓

agent.py

↓

Create ADK Session

↓

Create ADK Runner

↓

Gemini receives prompt

↓

Gemini analyses the request

↓

Gemini decides which MCP tools are required

↓

Invoke MCP server(s)

↓

Collect tool outputs

↓

Generate final response

↓

Return response to Flask

↓

Display response to user
```

The language model never performs the external work itself.

Instead, it orchestrates the available tools.

