# 3.5 Responsibilities of Each Component

## User Interface

Responsible for:

- Accepting user input
- Displaying AI responses
- Showing application status

The UI contains no business logic.

---

## Flask Backend

Responsible for:

- HTTP routing
- Request validation
- Invoking the AI agent
- Returning JSON responses

Flask is intentionally lightweight.

---

## agent.py

Responsible for:

- Loading environment variables
- Initializing Gemini
- Creating MCP toolsets
- Managing ADK sessions
- Running the AI workflow

This file represents the intelligence layer of the application.

---

## Google ADK

Responsible for:

- Managing conversations
- Managing tool execution
- Managing sessions
- Coordinating Gemini with MCP servers

ADK acts as the orchestration engine.

---

## Gemini Model

Responsible for:

- Understanding user intent
- Planning execution
- Selecting tools
- Combining tool outputs
- Producing the final response

Gemini performs reasoning only.

---

## MCP Servers

Responsible for:

- Executing specialized tasks

Examples:

Tavily

↓

University Search

Scholarship

↓

Scholarships

Visa

Cost of Living

Google Maps

↓

Weather

Nearby Attractions

Filesystem

↓

Markdown Report

Each MCP server performs one specialized function.

